# agent-loop.config — consumer-owned overrides for /agent-loop.
#
# Bootstrapped from a starter template on first sync; later upstream edits
# don't overwrite it (create_if_missing). Edit freely. Format is simple
# `key = value` lines (the loop script reads specific keys, not `source`d).
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# base_branch
#   The branch the loop builds its collection branch ON and targets the
#   end-of-run summary PR AGAINST. Leave it unset (commented out) to
#   auto-detect the repo's default branch via origin/HEAD — correct for
#   most repos.
#
#   Set it when your INTEGRATION branch differs from your DEFAULT branch —
#   e.g. a staging→main promotion flow where per-issue PRs target `staging`
#   but the GitHub default branch is `main`. Without this, the collection
#   branch is cut off `main` and the summary PR targets `main`, so its diff
#   is dominated by unpromoted backlog rather than the loop's work — and
#   merging it bypasses your promotion flow.
#
#   A one-off override is also available without editing this file:
#     AGENT_LOOP_BASE_BRANCH=staging .codex/skills/agent-loop/scripts/agent-loop.sh
#
# base_branch = staging

